 & =\sum_{m=0}^{k}\frac{\lambda^{k}}{k!}\exp(-\lambda)\frac{\mu^{k-m}}{(k-m)!}\exp(-\mu)\\
 & =\frac{1}{k!}\exp(-(\lambda+\mu))\sum_{m=0}^{k}\binom{k}{m}\lambda^{m}\mu^{k-m}=\frac{(\lambda+\mu)^{k}}{k!}\exp(-(\lambda+\mu)).
